==English==
===Noun===
''a'' '''[[blue]] [[moon]]'''

# The third [[full moon]] in a quarter of four full moons.
# (''rare'') The [[moon]] tinted towards [[blue]] as it appears in the sky.

===Etymology===
Mistake in Sky & Telescope magazine in 1946, retracted nearly 60 years later.

